    "body": "The main goal of this PR is to become independent of cooperative groups, since they don't work on nvc++ and seem to also have issues for the python wrappers. Also, since we have more information, we may discover a few fast paths.\r\n\r\nNext step is to replace the fallback in the UBLKCP kernel by the new memcpy_async as well, but not in this PR.\r\n\r\nMerge first:\r\n\r\n- [x] #2394 \r\n\r\nBenchmark on A100 shows benefits except one hickup in triad. I blame it on the GPU (I get hickups in different places on different machines).\r\n\r\n```\r\n# mul\r\n\r\n## [0] NVIDIA A100 80GB PCIe\r\n\r\n|  T{ct}  |  OffsetT{ct}  |  Elements{io}  |   Ref Time |   Ref Noise |   Cmp Time |   Cmp Noise |      Diff |   %Diff |  Status  |\r\n|---------|---------------|----------------|------------|-------------|------------|-------------|-----------|---------|----------|\r\n|   I8    |      I32      |      2^16      |   6.707 us |       8.00% |   6.577 us |       7.78% | -0.131 us |  -1.95% |   SAME   |\r\n|   I8    |      I32      |      2^20      |   8.338 us |       5.90% |   8.138 us |       6.49% | -0.200 us |  -2.40% |   SAME   |\r\n|   I8    |      I32      |      2^24      |  31.594 us |       1.77% |  30.674 us |       1.84% | -0.921 us |  -2.91% |   FAST   |\r\n|   I8    |      I32      |      2^28      | 371.379 us |       0.24% | 365.293 us |       0.25% | -6.085 us |  -1.64% |   FAST   |\r\n|   I8    |      I64      |      2^16      |   6.779 us |       8.98% |   6.626 us |       8.50% | -0.152 us |  -2.25% |   SAME   |\r\n|   I8    |      I64      |      2^20      |   8.285 us |       5.62% |   8.229 us |       6.25% | -0.056 us |  -0.68% |   SAME   |\r\n|   I8    |      I64      |      2^24      |  30.781 us |       1.69% |  30.555 us |       1.87% | -0.227 us |  -0.74% |   SAME   |\r\n|   I8    |      I64      |      2^28      | 370.566 us |       0.24% | 361.591 us |       0.28% | -8.974 us |  -2.42% |   FAST   |\r\n|   I16   |      I32      |      2^16